@startuml Crash Recovery with Exponential Backoff - Retry on Failure

title Crash Recovery: Supervised Retry with Exponential Backoff

participant Client as client
participant "CrashRecovery" as recovery
participant "Attempt 1\n(Virtual Thread)" as attempt1
participant "Attempt 2\n(Virtual Thread)" as attempt2
participant "Attempt 3\n(Virtual Thread)" as attempt3
participant "External\nService" as service

== Setup ==

client -> recovery: execute(() -> operation(), maxRetries=3, baseDelay=100ms)
note right of recovery
  Supplier<T> operation
  int maxRetries (number of retries after initial failure)
  long baseDelay (100ms minimum backoff)
end note

recovery -> recovery: initialize retryCount=0, delay=baseDelay

== Attempt 1 ==

recovery -> attempt1: spawn virtual thread
attempt1 -> service: call operation (e.g., fetch data)
service --> attempt1: timeout (transient failure)
attempt1 -> attempt1: throw TimeoutException
attempt1 -> recovery: exception propagated

recovery -> recovery: retryCount++
recovery -> recovery: catch exception
note right of recovery
  Not a fatal error
  Increment retry counter
end note

== Backoff: 2^0 * 100ms = 100ms ==

recovery -> recovery: sleep(100ms)

== Attempt 2 ==

recovery -> attempt2: spawn virtual thread
attempt2 -> service: call operation
service --> attempt2: connection refused (transient failure)
attempt2 -> attempt2: throw ConnectException
attempt2 -> recovery: exception propagated

recovery -> recovery: retryCount++
note right of recovery
  Still within maxRetries limit
  Compute next backoff
end note

== Backoff: 2^1 * 100ms = 200ms ==

recovery -> recovery: sleep(200ms)

== Attempt 3 ==

recovery -> attempt3: spawn virtual thread
attempt3 -> service: call operation
service --> attempt3: success (temporary issue resolved)
attempt3 -> attempt3: return result = "data"
attempt3 -> recovery: result returned

recovery -> recovery: success!
note right of recovery
  retryCount=2, maxRetries=3
  Within limit
  Operation succeeded
end note

recovery --> client: return result

== Failure Case ==

note over recovery, attempt3
  If Attempt 3 also failed:
  - retryCount would be 2
  - Would exceed maxRetries (3)
  - No more attempts
  - Throw last exception to client
  - Client must handle failure
end note

== Key Properties ==

note right of recovery
  Exponential Backoff Formula:
  delay(n) = baseDelay * 2^(n-1)
  - Attempt 1 fails
  - Wait 100ms (2^0 * 100)
  - Attempt 2 fails
  - Wait 200ms (2^1 * 100)
  - Attempt 3 fails
  - Wait 400ms (2^2 * 100)

  Prevents:
  1. Retry storms (pounding failing service)
  2. Thundering herd (all clients retry together)

  Isolation:
  - Each attempt in isolated virtual thread
  - Exception in one doesn't affect others
  - Thread cleanup automatic (virtual threads)
end note
